data.title: Not the best of Jack
data.text:
My preferred fast food is at Jack in the Box.  I've eaten them all over the U.S.

The local JIB on O'Connor in Irving is just ok.  They always take a while to have your order ready for you.  My wife and I went there today @ 1:30 pm and waited about ten minutes for our order.
Three other people were waiting ahead of us and I saw about five or six cars in the drive thru line.

I think since it is an older JIB maybe they have a smaller grill/prep area.  Either way, it takes longer that I'm used to for fast food.

Our burgers were good but a bit dry...even the Ultimate Cheeseburger with extra mayo.
